            "config": {
              "id": "QUE58892",
              "question": "Over the past several decades, cloning has been the topic of much heated debate in the United States. How would sociologist William Ogburn explain this culture war?\n\u003cbr /\u003e",
              "order": "randomized",
              "presenterType": "RadioGroup",
              "presenterConfig": {
                "numberFormat": "none"
              },
              "choices": [
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_1",
                  "content": "Ethnocentrism is inborn in humans, so cultures must learn to use cultural relativism."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "The conflict perspective is a much more useful tool to understanding culture than the symbolic interactionist perspective."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "Latent functions spread throughout a culture faster than manifest functions."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_4",
                  "content": "Material culture is generated faster than nonmaterial culture."
                }
              ]
            },
            "answerKey": {
              "assessmentType": "multiplechoice",
              "answers": {
                "answer_3": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Latent and manifest functions are key components of the functionalist perspective. Ogburn used the term cultural lag to explain how human behavior lags behind technological innovation. LO 2.6 Explain how technology changes culture and what cultural lag and cultural leveling are."
                },
                "answer_2": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Ogburn’s concept of cultural lag could be applied in both the conflict perspective and the symbolic interactionist perspective. LO 2.6 Explain how technology changes culture and what cultural lag and cultural leveling are."
                },
                "answer_1": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Ogburn used the term cultural lag to explain how human behavior lags behind technological innovation. Ethnocentrism and cultural relativism are used when judging other cultures. LO 2.6 Explain how technology changes culture and what cultural lag and cultural leveling are."
                },
                "answer_4": {
                  "score": 1.0,
                  "response": "That’s correct!"
                }
              }
            },
